{
  "text": "This distinction between the location of dental deviations in a single field and in several fields is essential for our insight into craniofacial syndromes. It is believed that the dentition will become central in diagnostics and evaluation of the pathogenesis behind craniofacial syndromes. In a recent paper, Trainor has highlighted the role of neural crest cells in the aetiology and pathogenesis of Treacher Collins syndrome and furthermore for the potential for prevention [CITATION_1] . We still need to know the genes responsible for neural crest cell migration.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "13748841"
